James Keith Doligol
Siyensikula
Siyensikula is a science video competition organized by the Department of Education (DepEd) in the Philippines. It is open to all Junior and Senior High School students from both public and private schools. This activity aims to promote science literacy among students, encourage students to be creative and innovative in their approach to science, and inspire students to pursue careers in science.
To participate in the Siyensikula competition, students must create a 3-minute video that discusses a science concept in a clear, creative, and engaging manner. The video must be original and must not contain any copyrighted materials.

Mechanics and Criteria

This contest is open to all Grade 10 to Grade 12 SRCCMSTHS Students.
Each section will be divided into groups.
The participants must discuss a difficult topic under Physical Sciences, Life Sciences, Mathematics or an Engineering concept in a clear, creative, and engaging way through video presentation that is not more than three (3) minutes. The participants may discuss the topic in English and/or Filipino.
All contents in the video must be original and are owned by the participants. These may include personal experiences and thoughtful observations. The video must reflect that the students have carefully reviewed and examined the topic.
All creative visual tools such as animations, simulations, physical demonstrations, or visual aids are allowed. List and cite all of the resources used such as images, audio, video clips, books, articles, etc. Use public domain sites for references and resources. Entries with derivative works will automatically be disqualified.
Entries must be submitted via google drive provided by their respective Science teacher with a subject format: “SIYENSIKULA_Grade&Section_VideoTitle” (ex. SIYENSIKULA_G11Passion_Ligtas)
The respective Science teacher along with the Science Department will choose the top5.
Entries will be evaluated using the Siyensikula Rubric Evaluation Tool.
The Champion, 1st runner-up, 2nd runner-up, 3rd runner-up, and 4th runner-up will be given a certificate for recognition. For non-winners, they will be receiving a certificate for participation.

hi eto pala ung steps forda CSS ^^

1. Connect the monitor to the power supply
2. Connect the system unit (CPU) to power supply
3. Connect the VGA port
4. Connect keyboard, mouse and speaker (back panel)
5. Plug and turn on the power button of the power supply then turn on the system unit and the monitor

TLDR:
1. Monitor to Power supply
2. CPU to Power Supply
3. VGA
4. Keyboard, mouse, speaker
5. Plug & turn on Power Supply before CPU then turn on monitor


diko sure sa steps 2-3 pero iirc sa sinabi ni maam mauuna muna ung mga icoconnect sa power supply bago ung VGA

Josher Clorion Morales
1st paragraph
Brief Overview/ Introduction ng Chapter
Main idea/Argument ng Author

2nd paragraph
Body: Evidences and reflection/personal reaction natin sa pinapakita ng author

3rd paragraph
Your personal comment about the author's way of writing the chapter

4th paragraph
Summarization & Conclusion of the chapter

Ralph Mateo
Sa pagkakaintindi ko, magsusulat tauo ng Review sa bawat chapter yung sinend dito sa gc. So, sa bawat chapter gagawa tayo ng parang reflection kung tungkol saan at ano yung pinag-uusapan sa chapter na yun?

Bale sa parts naman, sa Intro, kailangan muna natin isulat yung "Main Idea" or yung pinaparating ng author sa chapter na iyon?

Sa Body, dito na pwde i-summarize yung chapter?Pwede mag-lagay ng personal reaction natin?sa chapter?

Sinsasabi rin na mag-react raw sa way of writing, so kailangan magbigay ng opinyon? kung maganda at naiintindihan ba yung pagkakasulat?

Tapos sa Conclu naman, pwede na lang siguro isummarize yung intro at body dito, tapos pwede ilagay rito yung overall na natutunan at napulot sa chapter na sususlatan natn ngg review?

Magandang Umaga... Wala po ako ngayon ngunit mayroon kayong activity na gagawin.

Bumuo ng AKROSTIK, ito ay Isang uri ng tula na ang bawat taludtud ay nagsisimula sa mga letrang KOMUNIKASYON. halimbawa...

--------------- PAMAGAT ---------------
K - abataan ang pag-asa ng bayan ika nga ni Rizal,
U - maapaw raw ang pag-ibig sa bayan at
M - apagmahal pa raw sa wikang kinagisnan ngunit
U - mpisa nang mamulat
N - aging mapagmahal sa mga banyaga.
I - kinakatwa ang pagiging Pilipino
K - asuotan may nagbabago
A - nimoy malubhang sakit na unti-unting nagpapabulok rito
S - istema at paniniwala ay lubhang nagbago
Y - umayakap sa hindi naman sigurado
O - o mga kabataan Pilipino
N - aliligaw na nga kayo.

Ang tema ay tungkol sa wika. Isulat sa Isang buong papel at ilagay sa aking table sa library. Ito Rin ay magsisilbing attendance ninyo. Maraming salamat.
